      <hedline>
        <hl1>THE MARKETS: CURRENCIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>US dollar rises against euro as escalating violence in Middle East drives investors to currency's safety; graph; chart (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>THE DOLLAR GAINS. The dollar rose against the euro as escalating violence in the Middle East drove investors to the currency's safety. In New York, the euro settled at 86.22 cents, down from 86.88 cents on Wednesday.</p>
      </block>
